name: Men's 4x100
summary: The United States' long-standing reign in the men's 4x100-meter medley relay came to an end at the hands of China, with the US also facing disqualification in the 4x100-meter relay at the Paris Olympics due to a botched handoff. The 2024 Olympic finals for the 4x100-meter relay are set to take place on August 10, 2024. Despite the struggles of the US team, Canada emerged victorious in the men's 4x100-meter relay, while Caeleb Dressel and two swimmers from New Jersey contributed to a silver medal for the US in the men's 4x100-meter medley relay. The US team's disqualification has sparked discussions about potential changes to the relay system, emphasizing the importance of improving baton exchanges to avoid such setbacks in future competitions.
